				<h2>How does it work?</h2>
				<p class="text-justify">
					The whole thing is based on a clever use of the available APIs. What
					is happening behind the scene for every requests is the following:
					<ul>
						<li>We retrieve your current location or the location you are
						searching, plus the type of venues you are looking for and send it
						to our server </li>
						<li>From there, we get a list of relevant places from Yelp</li>
						<li>We add our own informations on top of those from Yelp</li>
						<li>Once the user has chosen a place, we get the most recent tweets
						that happened there, and the Instagram photos posted there</li>
					</ul>
				</p>
				<br>
